6030 // -fno-pack-struct doesn't apply to -fpack-struct=.
6031 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fpack_struct_EQ)) {
6032 std::string PackStructStr = "-fpack-struct=";
6033 PackStructStr += A->getValue();
6034 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(PackStructStr));
6035 } else if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fpack_struct,
6036 options::OPT_fno_pack_struct, false)) {
6037 CmdArgs.push_back("-fpack-struct=1");
6038 }
6039
6040 // Handle -fmax-type-align=N and -fno-type-align
6041 bool SkipMaxTypeAlign = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_max_type_align);
6042 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmax_type_align_EQ)) {
6043 if (!SkipMaxTypeAlign) {
6044 std::string MaxTypeAlignStr = "-fmax-type-align=";
6045 MaxTypeAlignStr += A->getValue();
6046 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(MaxTypeAlignStr));
6047 }
6048 } else if (RawTriple.isOSDarwin()) {
6049 if (!SkipMaxTypeAlign) {
6050 std::string MaxTypeAlignStr = "-fmax-type-align=16";
6051 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(MaxTypeAlignStr));
6052 }
6053 }
6054
6055 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_Qy, options::OPT_Qn, true))
6056 CmdArgs.push_back("-Qn");
6057
6058 // -fno-common is the default, set -fcommon only when that flag is set.
6059 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcommon, options::OPT_fno_common, false))
6060 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcommon");
6061
6062 // -fsigned-bitfields is default, and clang doesn't yet support
6063 // -funsigned-bitfields.
6064 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsigned_bitfields,
6065 options::OPT_funsigned_bitfields))
6066 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_clang_unsupported)
6067 << Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_funsigned_bitfields)->getAsString(Args);
6068
6069 // -fsigned-bitfields is default, and clang doesn't support -fno-for-scope.
6070 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_ffor_scope, options::OPT_fno_for_scope))
6071 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported)
6072 << Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fno_for_scope)->getAsString(Args);
6073
6074 // -finput_charset=UTF-8 is default. Reject others
6075 if (Arg *inputCharset = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_finput_charset_EQ)) {
6076 StringRef value = inputCharset->getValue();
6077 if (!value.equals_lower("utf-8"))
6078 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << inputCharset->getAsString(Args)
6079 << value;
6080 }
6081
6082 // -fexec_charset=UTF-8 is default. Reject others
6083 if (Arg *execCharset = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fexec_charset_EQ)) {
6084 StringRef value = execCharset->getValue();
6085 if (!value.equals_lower("utf-8"))
6086 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << execCharset->getAsString(Args)
6087 << value;
6088 }
6089
6090 RenderDiagnosticsOptions(D, Args, CmdArgs);
6091
6092 // -fno-asm-blocks is default.
6093 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fasm_blocks, options::OPT_fno_asm_blocks,
6094 false))
6095 CmdArgs.push_back("-fasm-blocks");
6096
6097 // -fgnu-inline-asm is default.
6098 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgnu_inline_asm,
6099 options::OPT_fno_gnu_inline_asm, true))
6100 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-gnu-inline-asm");
6101
6102 // Enable vectorization per default according to the optimization level
6103 // selected. For optimization levels that want vectorization we use the alias
6104 // option to simplify the hasFlag logic.
6105 bool EnableVec = shouldEnableVectorizerAtOLevel(Args, false);
6106 OptSpecifier VectorizeAliasOption =
6107 EnableVec ? options::OPT_O_Group : options::OPT_fvectorize;
6108 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fvectorize, VectorizeAliasOption,
6109 options::OPT_fno_vectorize, EnableVec))
6110 CmdArgs.push_back("-vectorize-loops");
6111
6112 // -fslp-vectorize is enabled based on the optimization level selected.
6113 bool EnableSLPVec = shouldEnableVectorizerAtOLevel(Args, true);
6114 OptSpecifier SLPVectAliasOption =
6115 EnableSLPVec ? options::OPT_O_Group : options::OPT_fslp_vectorize;
6116 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fslp_vectorize, SLPVectAliasOption,
6117 options::OPT_fno_slp_vectorize, EnableSLPVec))
6118 CmdArgs.push_back("-vectorize-slp");
6119
6120 ParseMPreferVectorWidth(D, Args, CmdArgs);
6121
6122 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fshow_overloads_EQ);
6123 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs,
6124 options::OPT_fsanitize_undefined_strip_path_components_EQ);
6125
6126 // -fdollars-in-identifiers default varies depending on platform and
6127 // language; only pass if specified.
6128 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fdollars_in_identifiers,
6129 options::OPT_fno_dollars_in_identifiers)) {
6130 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fdollars_in_identifiers))
6131 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdollars-in-identifiers");
6132 else
6133 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-dollars-in-identifiers");
6134 }
6135
6136 // -funit-at-a-time is default, and we don't support -fno-unit-at-a-time for
6137 // practical purposes.
6138 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_funit_at_a_time,
6139 options::OPT_fno_unit_at_a_time)) {
6140 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fno_unit_at_a_time))
6141 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_clang_unsupported) << A->getAsString(Args);
6142 }
6143
6144 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fapple_pragma_pack,
6145 options::OPT_fno_apple_pragma_pack, false))
6146 CmdArgs.push_back("-fapple-pragma-pack");
6147
6148 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fxl_pragma_pack,
6149 options::OPT_fno_xl_pragma_pack, RawTriple.isOSAIX()))
6150 CmdArgs.push_back("-fxl-pragma-pack");
6151
6152 // Remarks can be enabled with any of the `-f.*optimization-record.*` flags.
6153 if (willEmitRemarks(Args) && checkRemarksOptions(D, Args, Triple))
6154 renderRemarksOptions(Args, CmdArgs, Triple, Input, Output, JA);
6155
6156 bool RewriteImports = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_imports,
6157 options::OPT_fno_rewrite_imports, false);
6158 if (RewriteImports)
6159 CmdArgs.push_back("-frewrite-imports");
6160
6161 // Enable rewrite includes if the user's asked for it or if we're generating
6162 // diagnostics.
6163 // TODO: Once -module-dependency-dir works with -frewrite-includes it'd be
6164 // nice to enable this when doing a crashdump for modules as well.
6165 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_includes,
6166 options::OPT_fno_rewrite_includes, false) ||
6167 (C.isForDiagnostics() && !HaveModules))
6168 CmdArgs.push_back("-frewrite-includes");
6169
6170 // Only allow -traditional or -traditional-cpp outside in preprocessing modes.
6171 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_traditional,
6172 options::OPT_traditional_cpp)) {
6173 if (isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA))
6174 CmdArgs.push_back("-traditional-cpp");
6175 else
6176 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported) << A->getAsString(Args);
6177 }
6178
6179 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_dM);
6180 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_dD);
6181
6182 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmax_tokens_EQ);
6183
6184 // Handle serialized diagnostics.
6185 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__serialize_diags)) {
6186 CmdArgs.push_back("-serialize-diagnostic-file");
6187 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(A->getValue()));
6188 }
6189
6190 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fretain_comments_from_system_headers))
6191 CmdArgs.push_back("-fretain-comments-from-system-headers");
6192
6193 // Forward -fcomment-block-commands to -cc1.
6194 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fcomment_block_commands);
6195 // Forward -fparse-all-comments to -cc1.
6196 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fparse_all_comments);
6197
6198 // Turn -fplugin=name.so into -load name.so
6199 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_fplugin_EQ)) {
6200 CmdArgs.push_back("-load");
6201 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
6202 A->claim();
6203 }
6204
6205 // Forward -fpass-plugin=name.so to -cc1.
6206 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_fpass_plugin_EQ)) {
6207 CmdArgs.push_back(
6208 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fpass-plugin=") + A->getValue()));
6209 A->claim();
6210 }
6211
6212 // Setup statistics file output.
6213 SmallString<128> StatsFile = getStatsFileName(Args, Output, Input, D);
6214 if (!StatsFile.empty())
6215 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-stats-file=") + StatsFile));
6216
6217 // Forward -Xclang arguments to -cc1, and -mllvm arguments to the LLVM option
6218 // parser.
6219 // -finclude-default-header flag is for preprocessor,
6220 // do not pass it to other cc1 commands when save-temps is enabled
6221 if (C.getDriver().isSaveTempsEnabled() &&
6222 !isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA)) {
6223 for (auto Arg : Args.filtered(options::OPT_Xclang)) {
6224 Arg->claim();
6225 if (StringRef(Arg->getValue()) != "-finclude-default-header")
6226 CmdArgs.push_back(Arg->getValue());
6227 }
6228 }
6229 else {
6230 Args.AddAllArgValues(CmdArgs, options::OPT_Xclang);
6231 }
6232 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_mllvm)) {
6233 A->claim();
6234
6235 // We translate this by hand to the -cc1 argument, since nightly test uses
6236 // it and developers have been trained to spell it with -mllvm. Both
6237 // spellings are now deprecated and should be removed.
6238 if (StringRef(A->getValue(0)) == "-disable-llvm-optzns") {
6239 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-llvm-optzns");
6240 } else {
6241 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
6242 }
6243 }
6244
6245 // With -save-temps, we want to save the unoptimized bitcode output from the
6246 // CompileJobAction, use -disable-llvm-passes to get pristine IR generated
6247 // by the frontend.
6248 // When -fembed-bitcode is enabled, optimized bitcode is emitted because it
6249 // has slightly different breakdown between stages.
6250 // FIXME: -fembed-bitcode -save-temps will save optimized bitcode instead of
6251 // pristine IR generated by the frontend. Ideally, a new compile action should
6252 // be added so both IR can be captured.
6253 if ((C.getDriver().isSaveTempsEnabled() ||
6254 JA.isHostOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP)) &&
6255 !(C.getDriver().embedBitcodeInObject() && !C.getDriver().isUsingLTO()) &&
6256 isa<CompileJobAction>(JA))
6257 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-llvm-passes");
6258
6259 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_undef);
6260
6261 const char *Exec = D.getClangProgramPath();
6262
6263 // Optionally embed the -cc1 level arguments into the debug info or a
6264 // section, for build analysis.
6265 // Also record command line arguments into the debug info if
6266 // -grecord-gcc-switches options is set on.
6267 // By default, -gno-record-gcc-switches is set on and no recording.
6268 auto GRecordSwitches =
6269 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_grecord_command_line,
6270 options::OPT_gno_record_command_line, false);
6271 auto FRecordSwitches =
6272 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frecord_command_line,
6273 options::OPT_fno_record_command_line, false);
6274 if (FRecordSwitches && !Triple.isOSBinFormatELF())
6275 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target)
6276 << Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_frecord_command_line)->getAsString(Args)
6277 << TripleStr;
6278 if (TC.UseDwarfDebugFlags() || GRecordSwitches || FRecordSwitches) {
6279 ArgStringList OriginalArgs;
6280 for (const auto &Arg : Args)
6281 Arg->render(Args, OriginalArgs);
6282
6283 SmallString<256> Flags;
6284 EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(Exec, Flags);
6285 for (const char *OriginalArg : OriginalArgs) {
6286 SmallString<128> EscapedArg;
6287 EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(OriginalArg, EscapedArg);
6288 Flags += " ";
6289 Flags += EscapedArg;
6290 }
6291 auto FlagsArgString = Args.MakeArgString(Flags);
6292 if (TC.UseDwarfDebugFlags() || GRecordSwitches) {
6293 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-debug-flags");
6294 CmdArgs.push_back(FlagsArgString);
6295 }
6296 if (FRecordSwitches) {
6297 CmdArgs.push_back("-record-command-line");
6298 CmdArgs.push_back(FlagsArgString);
6299 }
6300 }
6301
6302 // Host-side cuda compilation receives all device-side outputs in a single
6303 // fatbin as Inputs[1]. Include the binary with -fcuda-include-gpubinary.
6304 if ((IsCuda || IsHIP) && CudaDeviceInput) {
6305 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcuda-include-gpubinary");
6306 CmdArgs.push_back(CudaDeviceInput->getFilename());
6307 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, false))
6308 CmdArgs.push_back("-fgpu-rdc");
6309 }
6310
6311 if (IsCuda) {
6312 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcuda_short_ptr,
6313 options::OPT_fno_cuda_short_ptr, false))
6314 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcuda-short-ptr");
6315 }
6316
6317 if (IsHIP)
6318 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcuda-allow-variadic-functions");
6319
6320 // OpenMP offloading device jobs take the argument -fopenmp-host-ir-file-path
6321 // to specify the result of the compile phase on the host, so the meaningful
6322 // device declarations can be identified. Also, -fopenmp-is-device is passed
6323 // along to tell the frontend that it is generating code for a device, so that
6324 // only the relevant declarations are emitted.
6325 if (IsOpenMPDevice) {
6326 CmdArgs.push_back("-fopenmp-is-device");
6327 if (OpenMPDeviceInput) {
6328 CmdArgs.push_back("-fopenmp-host-ir-file-path");
6329 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(OpenMPDeviceInput->getFilename()));
6330 }
6331 }
6332
6333 if (Triple.isAMDGPU()) {
6334 handleAMDGPUCodeObjectVersionOptions(D, Args, CmdArgs);
6335
6336 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_munsafe_fp_atomics,
6337 options::OPT_mno_unsafe_fp_atomics))
6338 CmdArgs.push_back("-munsafe-fp-atomics");
6339 }
6340
6341 // For all the host OpenMP offloading compile jobs we need to pass the targets
6342 // information using -fopenmp-targets= option.
6343 if (JA.isHostOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP)) {
6344 SmallString<128> TargetInfo("-fopenmp-targets=");
6345
6346 Arg *Tgts = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ);
6347 assert(Tgts && Tgts->getNumValues() &&
6348 "OpenMP offloading has to have targets specified.");
6349 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Tgts->getNumValues(); ++i) {
6350 if (i)
6351 TargetInfo += ',';
6352 // We need to get the string from the triple because it may be not exactly
6353 // the same as the one we get directly from the arguments.
6354 llvm::Triple T(Tgts->getValue(i));
6355 TargetInfo += T.getTriple();
6356 }
6357 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TargetInfo.str()));
6358 }
6359
6360 bool VirtualFunctionElimination =
6361 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fvirtual_function_elimination,
6362 options::OPT_fno_virtual_function_elimination, false);
6363 if (VirtualFunctionElimination) {
6364 // VFE requires full LTO (currently, this might be relaxed to allow ThinLTO
6365 // in the future).
6366 if (D.getLTOMode() != LTOK_Full)
6367 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
6368 << "-fvirtual-function-elimination"
6369 << "-flto=full";
6370
6371 CmdArgs.push_back("-fvirtual-function-elimination");
6372 }
6373
6374 // VFE requires whole-program-vtables, and enables it by default.
6375 bool WholeProgramVTables = Args.hasFlag(
6376 options::OPT_fwhole_program_vtables,
6377 options::OPT_fno_whole_program_vtables, VirtualFunctionElimination);
6378 if (VirtualFunctionElimination && !WholeProgramVTables) {
6379 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
6380 << "-fno-whole-program-vtables"
6381 << "-fvirtual-function-elimination";
6382 }
6383
6384 if (WholeProgramVTables) {
6385 if (!D.isUsingLTO())
6386 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
6387 << "-fwhole-program-vtables"
6388 << "-flto";
6389 CmdArgs.push_back("-fwhole-program-vtables");
6390 }
6391
6392 bool DefaultsSplitLTOUnit =
6393 (WholeProgramVTables || Sanitize.needsLTO()) &&
6394 (D.getLTOMode() == LTOK_Full || TC.canSplitThinLTOUnit());
6395 bool SplitLTOUnit =
6396 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsplit_lto_unit,
6397 options::OPT_fno_split_lto_unit, DefaultsSplitLTOUnit);
6398 if (Sanitize.needsLTO() && !SplitLTOUnit)
6399 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with) << "-fno-split-lto-unit"
6400 << "-fsanitize=cfi";
6401 if (SplitLTOUnit)
6402 CmdArgs.push_back("-fsplit-lto-unit");
6403
6404 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fglobal_isel,
6405 options::OPT_fno_global_isel)) {
6406 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
6407 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fglobal_isel)) {
6408 CmdArgs.push_back("-global-isel=1");
6409
6410 // GISel is on by default on AArch64 -O0, so don't bother adding
6411 // the fallback remarks for it. Other combinations will add a warning of
6412 // some kind.
6413 bool IsArchSupported = Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64;
6414 bool IsOptLevelSupported = false;
6415
6416 Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group);
6417 if (Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64) {
6418 if (!A || A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O0))
6419 IsOptLevelSupported = true;
6420 }
6421 if (!IsArchSupported || !IsOptLevelSupported) {
6422 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
6423 CmdArgs.push_back("-global-isel-abort=2");
6424
6425 if (!IsArchSupported)
6426 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_global_isel_incomplete) << Triple.getArchName();
6427 else
6428 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_global_isel_incomplete_opt);
6429 }
6430 } else {
6431 CmdArgs.push_back("-global-isel=0");
6432 }
6433 }
6434
6435 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_forder_file_instrumentation)) {
6436 CmdArgs.push_back("-forder-file-instrumentation");
6437 // Enable order file instrumentation when ThinLTO is not on. When ThinLTO is
6438 // on, we need to pass these flags as linker flags and that will be handled
6439 // outside of the compiler.
6440 if (!D.isUsingLTO()) {
6441 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
6442 CmdArgs.push_back("-enable-order-file-instrumentation");
6443 }
6444 }
6445
6446 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fforce_enable_int128,
6447 options::OPT_fno_force_enable_int128)) {
6448 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fforce_enable_int128))
6449 CmdArgs.push_back("-fforce-enable-int128");
6450 }
6451
6452 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fkeep_static_consts,
6453 options::OPT_fno_keep_static_consts, false))
6454 CmdArgs.push_back("-fkeep-static-consts");
6455
6456 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcomplete_member_pointers,
6457 options::OPT_fno_complete_member_pointers, false))
6458 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcomplete-member-pointers");
6459
6460 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcxx_static_destructors,
6461 options::OPT_fno_cxx_static_destructors, true))
6462 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-c++-static-destructors");
6463
6464 addMachineOutlinerArgs(D, Args, CmdArgs, Triple, /*IsLTO=*/false);
6465
6466 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_moutline_atomics,
6467 options::OPT_mno_outline_atomics)) {
6468 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_moutline_atomics)) {
6469 // Option -moutline-atomics supported for AArch64 target only.
6470 if (!Triple.isAArch64()) {
6471 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_moutline_atomics_unsupported_opt)
6472 << Triple.getArchName();
6473 } else {
6474 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
6475 CmdArgs.push_back("+outline-atomics");
6476 }
6477 } else {
6478 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
6479 CmdArgs.push_back("-outline-atomics");
6480 }
6481 }
6482
6483 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_faddrsig, options::OPT_fno_addrsig,
6484 (TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() ||
6485 TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) &&
6486 !TC.getTriple().isPS4() && !TC.getTriple().isVE() &&
6487 !TC.getTriple().isOSNetBSD() &&
6488 !Distro(D.getVFS(), TC.getTriple()).IsGentoo() &&
6489 !TC.getTriple().isAndroid() && TC.useIntegratedAs()))
6490 CmdArgs.push_back("-faddrsig");
6491
6492 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsymbol_partition_EQ)) {
6493 std::string Str = A->getAsString(Args);
6494 if (!TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF())
6495 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target)
6496 << Str << TC.getTripleString();
6497 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Str));
6498 }
6499
6500 // Add the "-o out -x type src.c" flags last. This is done primarily to make
6501 // the -cc1 command easier to edit when reproducing compiler crashes.
6502 if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Dependencies) {
6503 // Handled with other dependency code.
6504 } else if (Output.isFilename()) {
6505 if (Output.getType() == clang::driver::types::TY_IFS_CPP ||
6506 Output.getType() == clang::driver::types::TY_IFS) {
6507 SmallString<128> OutputFilename(Output.getFilename());
6508 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(OutputFilename, "ifs");
6509 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
6510 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(OutputFilename));
6511 } else {
6512 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
6513 CmdArgs.push_back(Output.getFilename());
6514 }
6515 } else {
6516 assert(Output.isNothing() && "Invalid output.");
6517 }
6518
6519 addDashXForInput(Args, Input, CmdArgs);
6520
6521 ArrayRef<InputInfo> FrontendInputs = Input;
6522 if (IsHeaderModulePrecompile)
6523 FrontendInputs = ModuleHeaderInputs;
6524 else if (Input.isNothing())
6525 FrontendInputs = {};
6526
6527 for (const InputInfo &Input : FrontendInputs) {
6528 if (Input.isFilename())
6529 CmdArgs.push_back(Input.getFilename());
6530 else
6531 Input.getInputArg().renderAsInput(Args, CmdArgs);
6532 }
6533
6534 // Finally add the compile command to the compilation.
6535 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback) &&
6536 Output.getType() == types::TY_Object &&
6537 (InputType == types::TY_C || InputType == types::TY_CXX)) {
6538 auto CLCommand =
6539 getCLFallback()->GetCommand(C, JA, Output, Inputs, Args, LinkingOutput);
6540 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<FallbackCommand>(
6541 JA, *this, ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(), Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs,
6542 Output, std::move(CLCommand)));
6543 } else if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback) &&
6544 isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA)) {
6545 // In /fallback builds, run the main compilation even if the pch generation
6546 // fails, so that the main compilation's fallback to cl.exe runs.
6547 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<ForceSuccessCommand>(
6548 JA, *this, ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(), Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs,
6549 Output));
6550 } else if (D.CC1Main && !D.CCGenDiagnostics) {
6551 // Invoke the CC1 directly in this process
6552 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<CC1Command>(JA, *this,
6553 ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(),
6554 Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs, Output));
6555 } else {
6556 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<Command>(JA, *this,
6557 ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(),
6558 Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs, Output));
6559 }
6560
6561 // Make the compile command echo its inputs for /showFilenames.
6562 if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Object &&
6563 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_showFilenames,
6564 options::OPT__SLASH_showFilenames_, false)) {
6565 C.getJobs().getJobs().back()->PrintInputFilenames = true;
6566 }
6567
6568 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_pg))
6569 if (FPKeepKind == CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::None &&
6570 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mfentry))
6571 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with) << "-fomit-frame-pointer"
6572 << A->getAsString(Args);
6573
6574 // Claim some arguments which clang supports automatically.
6575
6576 // -fpch-preprocess is used with gcc to add a special marker in the output to
6577 // include the PCH file.
6578 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fpch_preprocess);
6579
6580 // Claim some arguments which clang doesn't support, but we don't
6581 // care to warn the user about.
6582 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_clang_ignored_f_Group);
6583 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_clang_ignored_m_Group);
6584
6585 // Disable warnings for clang -E -emit-llvm foo.c
6586 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_emit_llvm);
6587}
6588
6589Clang::Clang(const ToolChain &TC)
6590 // CAUTION! The first constructor argument ("clang") is not arbitrary,
6591 // as it is for other tools. Some operations on a Tool actually test
6592 // whether that tool is Clang based on the Tool's Name as a string.
6593 : Tool("clang", "clang frontend", TC) {}
6594
6595Clang::~Clang() {}
6596
6597/// Add options related to the Objective-C runtime/ABI.
6598///
6599/// Returns true if the runtime is non-fragile.
6600ObjCRuntime Clang::AddObjCRuntimeArgs(const ArgList &args,
6601 const InputInfoList &inputs,
6602 ArgStringList &cmdArgs,
6603 RewriteKind rewriteKind) const {
6604 // Look for the controlling runtime option.
6605 Arg *runtimeArg =
6606 args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fnext_runtime, options::OPT_fgnu_runtime,
6607 options::OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ);
6608
6609 // Just forward -fobjc-runtime= to the frontend. This supercedes
6610 // options about fragility.
6611 if (runtimeArg &&
6612 runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ)) {
6613 ObjCRuntime runtime;
6614 StringRef value = runtimeArg->getValue();
6615 if (runtime.tryParse(value)) {
6616 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_unknown_objc_runtime)
6617 << value;
6618 }
6619 if ((runtime.getKind() == ObjCRuntime::GNUstep) &&
6620 (runtime.getVersion() >= VersionTuple(2, 0)))
6621 if (!getToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() &&
6622 !getToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6623 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(
6624 diag::err_drv_gnustep_objc_runtime_incompatible_binary)
6625 << runtime.getVersion().getMajor();
6626 }
6627
6628 runtimeArg->render(args, cmdArgs);
6629 return runtime;
6630 }
6631
6632 // Otherwise, we'll need the ABI "version". Version numbers are
6633 // slightly confusing for historical reasons:
6634 // 1 - Traditional "fragile" ABI
6635 // 2 - Non-fragile ABI, version 1
6636 // 3 - Non-fragile ABI, version 2
6637 unsigned objcABIVersion = 1;
6638 // If -fobjc-abi-version= is present, use that to set the version.
6639 if (Arg *abiArg = args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fobjc_abi_version_EQ)) {
6640 StringRef value = abiArg->getValue();
6641 if (value == "1")
6642 objcABIVersion = 1;
6643 else if (value == "2")
6644 objcABIVersion = 2;
6645 else if (value == "3")
6646 objcABIVersion = 3;
6647 else
6648 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported) << value;
6649 } else {
6650 // Otherwise, determine if we are using the non-fragile ABI.
6651 bool nonFragileABIIsDefault =
6652 (rewriteKind == RK_NonFragile ||
6653 (rewriteKind == RK_None &&
6654 getToolChain().IsObjCNonFragileABIDefault()));
6655 if (args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fobjc_nonfragile_abi,
6656 options::OPT_fno_objc_nonfragile_abi,
6657 nonFragileABIIsDefault)) {
6658// Determine the non-fragile ABI version to use.
6659#ifdef DISABLE_DEFAULT_NONFRAGILEABI_TWO
6660 unsigned nonFragileABIVersion = 1;
6661#else
6662 unsigned nonFragileABIVersion = 2;
6663#endif
6664
6665 if (Arg *abiArg =
6666 args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fobjc_nonfragile_abi_version_EQ)) {
6667 StringRef value = abiArg->getValue();
6668 if (value == "1")
6669 nonFragileABIVersion = 1;
6670 else if (value == "2")
6671 nonFragileABIVersion = 2;
6672 else
6673 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported)
6674 << value;
6675 }
6676
6677 objcABIVersion = 1 + nonFragileABIVersion;
6678 } else {
6679 objcABIVersion = 1;
6680 }
6681 }
6682
6683 // We don't actually care about the ABI version other than whether
6684 // it's non-fragile.
6685 bool isNonFragile = objcABIVersion != 1;
6686
6687 // If we have no runtime argument, ask the toolchain for its default runtime.
6688 // However, the rewriter only really supports the Mac runtime, so assume that.
6689 ObjCRuntime runtime;
6690 if (!runtimeArg) {
6691 switch (rewriteKind) {
6692 case RK_None:
6693 runtime = getToolChain().getDefaultObjCRuntime(isNonFragile);
6694 break;
6695 case RK_Fragile:
6696 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX, VersionTuple());
6697 break;
6698 case RK_NonFragile:
6699 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::MacOSX, VersionTuple());
6700 break;
6701 }
6702
6703 // -fnext-runtime
6704 } else if (runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fnext_runtime)) {
6705 // On Darwin, make this use the default behavior for the toolchain.
6706 if (getToolChain().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
6707 runtime = getToolChain().getDefaultObjCRuntime(isNonFragile);
6708
6709 // Otherwise, build for a generic macosx port.
6710 } else {
6711 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::MacOSX, VersionTuple());
6712 }
6713
6714 // -fgnu-runtime
6715 } else {
6716 assert(runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fgnu_runtime));
6717 // Legacy behaviour is to target the gnustep runtime if we are in
6718 // non-fragile mode or the GCC runtime in fragile mode.
6719 if (isNonFragile)
6720 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GNUstep, VersionTuple(2, 0));
6721 else
6722 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GCC, VersionTuple());
6723 }
6724
6725 if (llvm::any_of(inputs, [](const InputInfo &input) {
6726 return types::isObjC(input.getType());
6727 }))
6728 cmdArgs.push_back(
6729 args.MakeArgString("-fobjc-runtime=" + runtime.getAsString()));
6730 return runtime;
6731}
6732
6733static bool maybeConsumeDash(const std::string &EH, size_t &I) {
6734 bool HaveDash = (I + 1 < EH.size() && EH[I + 1] == '-');
6735 I += HaveDash;
6736 return !HaveDash;
6737}
6738
6739namespace {
6740struct EHFlags {
6741 bool Synch = false;
6742 bool Asynch = false;
6743 bool NoUnwindC = false;
6744};
6745} // end anonymous namespace
6746
6747/// /EH controls whether to run destructor cleanups when exceptions are
6748/// thrown. There are three modifiers:
6749/// - s: Cleanup after "synchronous" exceptions, aka C++ exceptions.
6750/// - a: Cleanup after "asynchronous" exceptions, aka structured exceptions.
6751/// The 'a' modifier is unimplemented and fundamentally hard in LLVM IR.
6752/// - c: Assume that extern "C" functions are implicitly nounwind.
6753/// The default is /EHs-c-, meaning cleanups are disabled.
6754static EHFlags parseClangCLEHFlags(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args) {
6755 EHFlags EH;
6756
6757 std::vector<std::string> EHArgs =
6758 Args.getAllArgValues(options::OPT__SLASH_EH);
6759 for (auto EHVal : EHArgs) {
6760 for (size_t I = 0, E = EHVal.size(); I != E; ++I) {
6761 switch (EHVal[I]) {
6762 case 'a':
6763 EH.Asynch = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
6764 if (EH.Asynch)
6765 EH.Synch = false;
6766 continue;
6767 case 'c':
6768 EH.NoUnwindC = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
6769 continue;
6770 case 's':
6771 EH.Synch = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
6772 if (EH.Synch)
6773 EH.Asynch = false;
6774 continue;
6775 default:
6776 break;
6777 }
6778 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << "/EH" << EHVal;
6779 break;
6780 }
6781 }
6782 // The /GX, /GX- flags are only processed if there are not /EH flags.
6783 // The default is that /GX is not specified.
6784 if (EHArgs.empty() &&
6785 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GX, options::OPT__SLASH_GX_,
6786 /*Default=*/false)) {
6787 EH.Synch = true;
6788 EH.NoUnwindC = true;
6789 }
6790
6791 return EH;
6792}
6793
6794void Clang::AddClangCLArgs(const ArgList &Args, types::ID InputType,
6795 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
6796 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind *DebugInfoKind,
6797 bool *EmitCodeView) const {
6798 unsigned RTOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_MT;
6799 bool isNVPTX = getToolChain().getTriple().isNVPTX();
6800
6801 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
6802 // The /LDd option implies /MTd. The dependent lib part can be overridden,
6803 // but defining _DEBUG is sticky.
6804 RTOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_MTd;
6805
6806 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_M_Group))
6807 RTOptionID = A->getOption().getID();
6808
6809 StringRef FlagForCRT;
6810 switch (RTOptionID) {
6811 case options::OPT__SLASH_MD:
6812 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
6813 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
6814 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
6815 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DLL");
6816 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=msvcrt";
6817 break;
6818 case options::OPT__SLASH_MDd:
6819 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
6820 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
6821 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DLL");
6822 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=msvcrtd";
6823 break;
6824 case options::OPT__SLASH_MT:
6825 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
6826 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
6827 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
6828 CmdArgs.push_back("-flto-visibility-public-std");
6829 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=libcmt";
6830 break;
6831 case options::OPT__SLASH_MTd:
6832 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
6833 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
6834 CmdArgs.push_back("-flto-visibility-public-std");
6835 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=libcmtd";
6836 break;
6837 default:
6838 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected option ID.");
6839 }
6840
6841 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Zl)) {
6842 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_VC_NODEFAULTLIB");
6843 } else {
6844 CmdArgs.push_back(FlagForCRT.data());
6845
6846 // This provides POSIX compatibility (maps 'open' to '_open'), which most
6847 // users want. The /Za flag to cl.exe turns this off, but it's not
6848 // implemented in clang.
6849 CmdArgs.push_back("--dependent-lib=oldnames");
6850 }
6851
6852 if (Arg *ShowIncludes =
6853 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_showIncludes,
6854 options::OPT__SLASH_showIncludes_user)) {
6855 CmdArgs.push_back("--show-includes");
6856 if (ShowIncludes->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_showIncludes))
6857 CmdArgs.push_back("-sys-header-deps");
6858 }
6859
6860 // This controls whether or not we emit RTTI data for polymorphic types.
6861 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GR_, options::OPT__SLASH_GR,
6862 /*Default=*/false))
6863 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-rtti-data");
6864
6865 // This controls whether or not we emit stack-protector instrumentation.
6866 // In MSVC, Buffer Security Check (/GS) is on by default.
6867 if (!isNVPTX && Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GS, options::OPT__SLASH_GS_,
6868 /*Default=*/true)) {
6869 CmdArgs.push_back("-stack-protector");
6870 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine(LangOptions::SSPStrong)));
6871 }
6872
6873 // Emit CodeView if -Z7 or -gline-tables-only are present.
6874 if (Arg *DebugInfoArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Z7,
6875 options::OPT_gline_tables_only)) {
6876 *EmitCodeView = true;
6877 if (DebugInfoArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Z7))
6878 *DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo;
6879 else
6880 *DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly;
6881 } else {
6882 *EmitCodeView = false;
6883 }
6884
6885 const Driver &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
6886 EHFlags EH = parseClangCLEHFlags(D, Args);
6887 if (!isNVPTX && (EH.Synch || EH.Asynch)) {
6888 if (types::isCXX(InputType))
6889 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcxx-exceptions");
6890 CmdArgs.push_back("-fexceptions");
6891 }
6892 if (types::isCXX(InputType) && EH.Synch && EH.NoUnwindC)
6893 CmdArgs.push_back("-fexternc-nounwind");
6894
6895 // /EP should expand to -E -P.
6896 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP)) {
6897 CmdArgs.push_back("-E");
6898 CmdArgs.push_back("-P");
6899 }
6900
6901 unsigned VolatileOptionID;
6902 if (getToolChain().getTriple().isX86())
6903 VolatileOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_ms;
6904 else
6905 VolatileOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_iso;
6906
6907 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_Group))
6908 VolatileOptionID = A->getOption().getID();
6909
6910 if (VolatileOptionID == options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_ms)
6911 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-volatile");
6912
6913 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_Zc_dllexportInlines_,
6914 options::OPT__SLASH_Zc_dllexportInlines,
6915 false)) {
6916 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback)) {
6917 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_dllexport_inlines_and_fallback);
6918 } else {
6919 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-dllexport-inlines");
6920 }
6921 }
6922
6923 Arg *MostGeneralArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmg);
6924 Arg *BestCaseArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmb);
6925 if (MostGeneralArg && BestCaseArg)
6926 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
6927 << MostGeneralArg->getAsString(Args) << BestCaseArg->getAsString(Args);
6928
6929 if (MostGeneralArg) {
6930 Arg *SingleArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vms);
6931 Arg *MultipleArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmm);
6932 Arg *VirtualArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmv);
6933
6934 Arg *FirstConflict = SingleArg ? SingleArg : MultipleArg;
6935 Arg *SecondConflict = VirtualArg ? VirtualArg : MultipleArg;
6936 if (FirstConflict && SecondConflict && FirstConflict != SecondConflict)
6937 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
6938 << FirstConflict->getAsString(Args)
6939 << SecondConflict->getAsString(Args);
6940
6941 if (SingleArg)
6942 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=single");
6943 else if (MultipleArg)
6944 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=multiple");
6945 else
6946 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=virtual");
6947 }
6948
6949 // Parse the default calling convention options.
6950 if (Arg *CCArg =
6951 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Gd, options::OPT__SLASH_Gr,
6952 options::OPT__SLASH_Gz, options::OPT__SLASH_Gv,
6953 options::OPT__SLASH_Gregcall)) {
6954 unsigned DCCOptId = CCArg->getOption().getID();
6955 const char *DCCFlag = nullptr;
6956 bool ArchSupported = !isNVPTX;
6957 llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = getToolChain().getArch();
6958 switch (DCCOptId) {
6959 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gd:
6960 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=cdecl";
6961 break;
6962 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gr:
6963 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86;
6964 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=fastcall";
6965 break;
6966 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gz:
6967 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86;
6968 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=stdcall";
6969 break;
6970 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gv:
6971 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86 || Arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64;
6972 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=vectorcall";
6973 break;
6974 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gregcall:
6975 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86 || Arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64;
6976 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=regcall";
6977 break;
6978 }
6979
6980 // MSVC doesn't warn if /Gr or /Gz is used on x64, so we don't either.
6981 if (ArchSupported && DCCFlag)
6982 CmdArgs.push_back(DCCFlag);
6983 }
6984
6985 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_vtordisp_mode_EQ);
6986
6987 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fdiagnostics_format_EQ)) {
6988 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdiagnostics-format");
6989 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback))
6990 CmdArgs.push_back("msvc-fallback");
6991 else
6992 CmdArgs.push_back("msvc");
6993 }
6994
6995 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_guard)) {
6996 StringRef GuardArgs = A->getValue();
6997 // The only valid options are "cf", "cf,nochecks", and "cf-".
6998 if (GuardArgs.equals_lower("cf")) {
6999 // Emit CFG instrumentation and the table of address-taken functions.
7000 CmdArgs.push_back("-cfguard");
7001 } else if (GuardArgs.equals_lower("cf,nochecks")) {
7002 // Emit only the table of address-taken functions.
7003 CmdArgs.push_back("-cfguard-no-checks");
7004 } else if (GuardArgs.equals_lower("cf-")) {
7005 // Do nothing, but we might want to emit a security warning in future.
7006 } else {
7007 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getSpelling() << GuardArgs;
7008 }
7009 }
7010}
7011
7012visualstudio::Compiler *Clang::getCLFallback() const {
7013 if (!CLFallback)
7014 CLFallback.reset(new visualstudio::Compiler(getToolChain()));
7015 return CLFallback.get();
7016}
7017
7018
7019const char *Clang::getBaseInputName(const ArgList &Args,
7020 const InputInfo &Input) {
7021 return Args.MakeArgString(llvm::sys::path::filename(Input.getBaseInput()));
7022}
7023
7024const char *Clang::getBaseInputStem(const ArgList &Args,
7025 const InputInfoList &Inputs) {
7026 const char *Str = getBaseInputName(Args, Inputs[0]);
7027
7028 if (const char *End = strrchr(Str, '.'))
7029 return Args.MakeArgString(std::string(Str, End));
7030
7031 return Str;
7032}
7033
7034const char *Clang::getDependencyFileName(const ArgList &Args,
7035 const InputInfoList &Inputs) {
7036 // FIXME: Think about this more.
7037
7038 if (Arg *OutputOpt = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_o)) {
7039 SmallString<128> OutputFilename(OutputOpt->getValue());
7040 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(OutputFilename, llvm::Twine('d'));
7041 return Args.MakeArgString(OutputFilename);
7042 }
7043
7044 return Args.MakeArgString(Twine(getBaseInputStem(Args, Inputs)) + ".d");
7045}

7049void ClangAs::AddMIPSTargetArgs(const ArgList &Args,
7050 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) const {
7051 StringRef CPUName;
7052 StringRef ABIName;
7053 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getTriple();
7054 mips::getMipsCPUAndABI(Args, Triple, CPUName, ABIName);
7055
7056 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-abi");
7057 CmdArgs.push_back(ABIName.data());
7058}
7059
7060void ClangAs::AddX86TargetArgs(const ArgList &Args,
7061 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) const {
7062 addX86AlignBranchArgs(getToolChain().getDriver(), Args, CmdArgs,
7063 /*IsLTO=*/false);
7064
7065 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_masm_EQ)) {
7066 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
7067 if (Value == "intel" || Value == "att") {
7068 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
7069 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-x86-asm-syntax=" + Value));
7070 } else {
7071 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
7072 << A->getOption().getName() << Value;
7073 }
7074 }
7075}

7078 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) const {
7079 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getTriple();
7080 StringRef ABIName = riscv::getRISCVABI(Args, Triple);
7081
7082 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-abi");
7083 CmdArgs.push_back(ABIName.data());
7084}
7085
7086void ClangAs::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
7087 const InputInfo &Output, const InputInfoList &Inputs,
7088 const ArgList &Args,
7089 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
7090 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
7091
7092 assert(Inputs.size() == 1 && "Unexpected number of inputs.");
7093 const InputInfo &Input = Inputs[0];
7094
7095 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getEffectiveTriple();
7096 const std::string &TripleStr = Triple.getTriple();
7097 const auto &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
7098
7099 // Don't warn about "clang -w -c foo.s"
7100 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_w);
7101 // and "clang -emit-llvm -c foo.s"
7102 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_emit_llvm);
7103
7104 claimNoWarnArgs(Args);
7105
7106 // Invoke ourselves in -cc1as mode.
7107 //
7108 // FIXME: Implement custom jobs for internal actions.
7109 CmdArgs.push_back("-cc1as");
7110
7111 // Add the "effective" target triple.
7112 CmdArgs.push_back("-triple");
7113 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TripleStr));
7114
7115 // Set the output mode, we currently only expect to be used as a real
7116 // assembler.
7117 CmdArgs.push_back("-filetype");
7118 CmdArgs.push_back("obj");
7119
7120 // Set the main file name, so that debug info works even with
7121 // -save-temps or preprocessed assembly.
7122 CmdArgs.push_back("-main-file-name");
7123 CmdArgs.push_back(Clang::getBaseInputName(Args, Input));
7124
7125 // Add the target cpu
7126 std::string CPU = getCPUName(Args, Triple, /*FromAs*/ true);
7127 if (!CPU.empty()) {
7128 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-cpu");
7129 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(CPU));
7130 }
7131
7132 // Add the target features
7133 getTargetFeatures(D, Triple, Args, CmdArgs, true);
7134
7135 // Ignore explicit -force_cpusubtype_ALL option.
7136 (void)Args.hasArg(options::OPT_force__cpusubtype__ALL);
7137
7138 // Pass along any -I options so we get proper .include search paths.
7139 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_I_Group);
7140
7141 // Determine the original source input.
7142 const Action *SourceAction = &JA;
7143 while (SourceAction->getKind() != Action::InputClass) {
7144 assert(!SourceAction->getInputs().empty() && "unexpected root action!");
7145 SourceAction = SourceAction->getInputs()[0];
7146 }
7147
7148 // Forward -g and handle debug info related flags, assuming we are dealing
7149 // with an actual assembly file.
7150 bool WantDebug = false;
7151 unsigned DwarfVersion = 0;
7152 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_g_Group);
7153 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_g_Group)) {
7154 WantDebug = !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_g0) &&
7155 !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_ggdb0);
7156 if (WantDebug)
7157 DwarfVersion = DwarfVersionNum(A->getSpelling());
7158 }
7159
7160 unsigned DefaultDwarfVersion = ParseDebugDefaultVersion(getToolChain(), Args);
7161 if (DwarfVersion == 0)
7162 DwarfVersion = DefaultDwarfVersion;
7163
7164 if (DwarfVersion == 0)
7165 DwarfVersion = getToolChain().GetDefaultDwarfVersion();
7166
7167 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
7168
7169 if (SourceAction->getType() == types::TY_Asm ||
7170 SourceAction->getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm) {
7171 // You might think that it would be ok to set DebugInfoKind outside of
7172 // the guard for source type, however there is a test which asserts
7173 // that some assembler invocation receives no -debug-info-kind,
7174 // and it's not clear whether that test is just overly restrictive.
7175 DebugInfoKind = (WantDebug ? codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo
7176 : codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo);
7177 // Add the -fdebug-compilation-dir flag if needed.
7178 addDebugCompDirArg(Args, CmdArgs, C.getDriver().getVFS());
7179
7180 addDebugPrefixMapArg(getToolChain().getDriver(), Args, CmdArgs);
7181
7182 // Set the AT_producer to the clang version when using the integrated
7183 // assembler on assembly source files.
7184 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-debug-producer");
7185 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(getClangFullVersion()));
7186
7187 // And pass along -I options
7188 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_I);
7189 }
7190 RenderDebugEnablingArgs(Args, CmdArgs, DebugInfoKind, DwarfVersion,
7191 llvm::DebuggerKind::Default);
7192 RenderDebugInfoCompressionArgs(Args, CmdArgs, D, getToolChain());
7193
7194
7195 // Handle -fPIC et al -- the relocation-model affects the assembler
7196 // for some targets.
7197 llvm::Reloc::Model RelocationModel;
7198 unsigned PICLevel;
7199 bool IsPIE;
7200 std::tie(RelocationModel, PICLevel, IsPIE) =
7201 ParsePICArgs(getToolChain(), Args);
7202
7203 const char *RMName = RelocationModelName(RelocationModel);
7204 if (RMName) {
7205 CmdArgs.push_back("-mrelocation-model");
7206 CmdArgs.push_back(RMName);
7207 }
7208
7209 // Optionally embed the -cc1as level arguments into the debug info, for build
7210 // analysis.
7211 if (getToolChain().UseDwarfDebugFlags()) {
7212 ArgStringList OriginalArgs;
7213 for (const auto &Arg : Args)
7214 Arg->render(Args, OriginalArgs);
7215
7216 SmallString<256> Flags;
7217 const char *Exec = getToolChain().getDriver().getClangProgramPath();
7218 EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(Exec, Flags);
7219 for (const char *OriginalArg : OriginalArgs) {
7220 SmallString<128> EscapedArg;
7221 EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(OriginalArg, EscapedArg);
7222 Flags += " ";
7223 Flags += EscapedArg;
7224 }
7225 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-debug-flags");
7226 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Flags));
7227 }
7228
7229 // FIXME: Add -static support, once we have it.
7230
7231 // Add target specific flags.
7232 switch (getToolChain().getArch()) {
7233 default:
7234 break;
7235
7236 case llvm::Triple::mips:
7237 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
7238 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
7239 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
7240 AddMIPSTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
7241 break;
7242
7243 case llvm::Triple::x86:
7244 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
7245 AddX86TargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
7246 break;
7247
7248 case llvm::Triple::arm:
7249 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
7250 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
7251 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
7252 // This isn't in AddARMTargetArgs because we want to do this for assembly
7253 // only, not C/C++.
7254 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mdefault_build_attributes,
7255 options::OPT_mno_default_build_attributes, true)) {
7256 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
7257 CmdArgs.push_back("-arm-add-build-attributes");
7258 }
7259 break;
7260
7261 case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
7262 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_32:
7263 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
7264 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mmark_bti_property)) {
7265 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
7266 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-mark-bti-property");
7267 }
7268 break;
7269
7270 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
7271 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
7272 AddRISCVTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
7273 break;
7274 }
7275
7276 // Consume all the warning flags. Usually this would be handled more
7277 // gracefully by -cc1 (warning about unknown warning flags, etc) but -cc1as
7278 // doesn't handle that so rather than warning about unused flags that are
7279 // actually used, we'll lie by omission instead.
7280 // FIXME: Stop lying and consume only the appropriate driver flags
7281 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_W_Group);
7282
7283 CollectArgsForIntegratedAssembler(C, Args, CmdArgs,
7284 getToolChain().getDriver());
7285
7286 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_mllvm);
7287
7288 assert(Output.isFilename() && "Unexpected lipo output.");
7289 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
7290 CmdArgs.push_back(Output.getFilename());
7291
7292 const llvm::Triple &T = getToolChain().getTriple();
7293 Arg *A;
7294 if (getDebugFissionKind(D, Args, A) == DwarfFissionKind::Split &&
7295 T.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
7296 CmdArgs.push_back("-split-dwarf-output");
7297 CmdArgs.push_back(SplitDebugName(JA, Args, Input, Output));
7298 }
7299
7300 if (Triple.isAMDGPU())
7301 handleAMDGPUCodeObjectVersionOptions(D, Args, CmdArgs);
7302
7303 assert(Input.isFilename() && "Invalid input.");
7304 CmdArgs.push_back(Input.getFilename());
7305
7306 const char *Exec = getToolChain().getDriver().getClangProgramPath();
7307 if (D.CC1Main && !D.CCGenDiagnostics) {
7308 // Invoke cc1as directly in this process.
7309 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<CC1Command>(JA, *this,
7310 ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(),
7311 Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs, Output));
7312 } else {
7313 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<Command>(JA, *this,
7314 ResponseFileSupport::AtFileUTF8(),
7315 Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs, Output));
7316 }
7317}
7318
7319// Begin OffloadBundler
7320
7321void OffloadBundler::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
7322 const InputInfo &Output,
7323 const InputInfoList &Inputs,
7324 const llvm::opt::ArgList &TCArgs,
7325 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
7326 // The version with only one output is expected to refer to a bundling job.
7327 assert(isa<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(JA) && "Expecting bundling job!");
7328
7329 // The bundling command looks like this:
7330 // clang-offload-bundler -type=bc
7331 // -targets=host-triple,openmp-triple1,openmp-triple2
7332 // -outputs=input_file
7333 // -inputs=unbundle_file_host,unbundle_file_tgt1,unbundle_file_tgt2"
7334
7335 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
7336
7337 // Get the type.
7338 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(
7339 Twine("-type=") + types::getTypeTempSuffix(Output.getType())));
7340
7341 assert(JA.getInputs().size() == Inputs.size() &&
7342 "Not have inputs for all dependence actions??");
7343
7344 // Get the targets.
7345 SmallString<128> Triples;
7346 Triples += "-targets=";
7347 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Inputs.size(); ++I) {
7348 if (I)
7349 Triples += ',';
7350
7351 // Find ToolChain for this input.
7352 Action::OffloadKind CurKind = Action::OFK_Host;
7353 const ToolChain *CurTC = &getToolChain();
7354 const Action *CurDep = JA.getInputs()[I];
7355
7356 if (const auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(CurDep)) {
7357 CurTC = nullptr;
7358 OA->doOnEachDependence([&](Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, const char *) {
7359 assert(CurTC == nullptr && "Expected one dependence!");
7360 CurKind = A->getOffloadingDeviceKind();
7361 CurTC = TC;
7362 });
7363 }
7364 Triples += Action::GetOffloadKindName(CurKind);
7365 Triples += '-';
7366 Triples += CurTC->getTriple().normalize();
7367 if (CurKind == Action::OFK_HIP && CurDep->getOffloadingArch()) {
7368 Triples += '-';
7369 Triples += CurDep->getOffloadingArch();
7370 }
7371 }
7372 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(Triples));
7373
7374 // Get bundled file command.
7375 CmdArgs.push_back(
7376 TCArgs.MakeArgString(Twine("-outputs=") + Output.getFilename()));
7377
7378 // Get unbundled files command.
7379 SmallString<128> UB;
7380 UB += "-inputs=";
7381 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Inputs.size(); ++I) {
7382 if (I)
7383 UB += ',';
7384
7385 // Find ToolChain for this input.
7386 const ToolChain *CurTC = &getToolChain();
7387 if (const auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(JA.getInputs()[I])) {
7388 CurTC = nullptr;
7389 OA->doOnEachDependence([&](Action *, const ToolChain *TC, const char *) {
7390 assert(CurTC == nullptr && "Expected one dependence!");
7391 CurTC = TC;
7392 });
7393 }
7394 UB += CurTC->getInputFilename(Inputs[I]);
7395 }
7396 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(UB));
7397
7398 // All the inputs are encoded as commands.
7399 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<Command>(
7400 JA, *this, ResponseFileSupport::None(),
7401 TCArgs.MakeArgString(getToolChain().GetProgramPath(getShortName())),
7402 CmdArgs, None, Output));
7403}
7404
7405void OffloadBundler::ConstructJobMultipleOutputs(
7406 Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA, const InputInfoList &Outputs,
7407 const InputInfoList &Inputs, const llvm::opt::ArgList &TCArgs,
7408 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
7409 // The version with multiple outputs is expected to refer to a unbundling job.
7410 auto &UA = cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(JA);
7411
7412 // The unbundling command looks like this:
7413 // clang-offload-bundler -type=bc
7414 // -targets=host-triple,openmp-triple1,openmp-triple2
7415 // -inputs=input_file
7416 // -outputs=unbundle_file_host,unbundle_file_tgt1,unbundle_file_tgt2"
7417 // -unbundle
7418
7419 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
7420
7421 assert(Inputs.size() == 1 && "Expecting to unbundle a single file!");
7422 InputInfo Input = Inputs.front();
7423
7424 // Get the type.
7425 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(
7426 Twine("-type=") + types::getTypeTempSuffix(Input.getType())));
7427
7428 // Get the targets.
7429 SmallString<128> Triples;
7430 Triples += "-targets=";
7431 auto DepInfo = UA.getDependentActionsInfo();
7432 for (unsigned I = 0; I < DepInfo.size(); ++I) {
7433 if (I)
7434 Triples += ',';
7435
7436 auto &Dep = DepInfo[I];
7437 Triples += Action::GetOffloadKindName(Dep.DependentOffloadKind);
7438 Triples += '-';
7439 Triples += Dep.DependentToolChain->getTriple().normalize();
7440 if (Dep.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP &&
7441 !Dep.DependentBoundArch.empty()) {
7442 Triples += '-';
7443 Triples += Dep.DependentBoundArch;
7444 }
7445 }
7446
7447 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(Triples));
7448
7449 // Get bundled file command.
7450 CmdArgs.push_back(
7451 TCArgs.MakeArgString(Twine("-inputs=") + Input.getFilename()));
7452
7453 // Get unbundled files command.
7454 SmallString<128> UB;
7455 UB += "-outputs=";
7456 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Outputs.size(); ++I) {
7457 if (I)
7458 UB += ',';
7459 UB += DepInfo[I].DependentToolChain->getInputFilename(Outputs[I]);
7460 }
7461 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(UB));
7462 CmdArgs.push_back("-unbundle");
7463 CmdArgs.push_back("-allow-missing-bundles");
7464
7465 // All the inputs are encoded as commands.
7466 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<Command>(
7467 JA, *this, ResponseFileSupport::None(),
7468 TCArgs.MakeArgString(getToolChain().GetProgramPath(getShortName())),
7469 CmdArgs, None, Outputs));
7470}
7471
7472void OffloadWrapper::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
7473 const InputInfo &Output,
7474 const InputInfoList &Inputs,
7475 const ArgList &Args,
7476 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
7477 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
7478
7479 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getEffectiveTriple();
7480
7481 // Add the "effective" target triple.
7482 CmdArgs.push_back("-target");
7483 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Triple.getTriple()));
7484
7485 // Add the output file name.
7486 assert(Output.isFilename() && "Invalid output.");
7487 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
7488 CmdArgs.push_back(Output.getFilename());
7489
7490 // Add inputs.
7491 for (const InputInfo &I : Inputs) {
7492 assert(I.isFilename() && "Invalid input.");
7493 CmdArgs.push_back(I.getFilename());
7494 }
7495
7496 C.addCommand(std::make_unique<Command>(
7497 JA, *this, ResponseFileSupport::None(),
7498 Args.MakeArgString(getToolChain().GetProgramPath(getShortName())),
7499 CmdArgs, Inputs, Output));
7500}
